\f1\b0\fs52 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups all-purpose flour\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon baking powder\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 kosher salt}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 pound (1 stick) cold unsalted butter, diced\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup half-and-half\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup chopped fresh chives or fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 parsley}} leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 egg mixed with 1 tablespoon water, for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/egg-wash/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 egg wash}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs62 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs52 \cf2 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.\
Combine the flour, baking powder, salt, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sugar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 sugar}} in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Add the butter and mix on low speed until the butter is the size of peas. With the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 mixer}} on low, add the half-and-half and beat until just mixed. Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chives/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 chives}} and mix until just combined.\
Dump the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dough/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 dough}} out on a well-floured board and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/knead/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 knead}} lightly into a rectangle 3/4-inch thick. Cut out rounds with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter and place on a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sheet-pan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 sheet pan}} lined with parchment paper. Brush with the egg wash.\
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes, until the tops are browned and the insides are firm. Serve warm.\
